    <h1>Rectangle Body</h1>

    <h2>Rectangle Body Type for Females</h2>

    <h3>Body Type Description:</h3>
    <p>The rectangle body type, also known as the "straight" or "athletic" body type, is characterized by similar measurements for the bust, waist, and hips. Women with this body type typically have a more athletic build with less defined curves. The overall silhouette appears straight up and down, lacking a significant waist definition. The rectangle body type is often associated with a lean appearance and is typically athletic in nature, making it easier for individuals to build muscle.</p>

    <h3>Food List for Rectangle Body Type Females:</h3>
    <p>To support a healthy body composition and maintain muscle while enhancing curves, a balanced diet rich in whole foods is essential. The recommended macronutrient breakdown for rectangle body types is generally 40% carbs, 30% protein, and 30% fat.</p>

    <h4>Meat and Fish:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Lean meats (chicken breast, turkey, lean beef)</li>
        <li>Fish (salmon, tuna)</li>
        <li>Eggs</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Dairy:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Low-fat yogurt</li>
        <li>Cottage cheese</li>
        <li>Almond or soy milk</li>
    </ul>

