    <h2>Advantages of the Rectangle Body Type Diet</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Balanced Nutritional Intake: A varied diet helps maintain a healthy body composition while supporting muscle growth.</li>
        <li>Flexibility in Food Choices: The emphasis on whole foods allows for diverse meal options, making it easier to stick to a plan.</li>
        <li>Muscle Maintenance: Adequate protein intake supports muscle retention, which is crucial for overall metabolism and body composition.</li>
        <li>Weight Management: A focus on whole foods and balanced macronutrients aids in managing weight effectively.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Workout Recommendations for Rectangle Body Type Females</h2>
    <p><strong>Strength Training:</strong> Focus on exercises that build muscle and enhance curves, such as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Squats and lunges to target the lower body</li>
        <li>Deadlifts for overall strength</li>
        <li>Upper body workouts (e.g., push-ups, shoulder presses) to create definition</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Cardiovascular Exercise:</strong> Engage in moderate-intensity cardio, such as running, cycling, or swimming, for at least 150 minutes per week to promote heart health and manage weight.</p>
    <p><strong>High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT):</strong> Incorporate HIIT workouts 1-2 times a week for improved endurance and effective calorie burning.</p>
    <p><strong>Flexibility and Core Work:</strong> Include activities like yoga or Pilates to enhance flexibility, core strength, and posture.</p>

